<p>
<seg id=1> Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu appointed Sharon, the No. 1 hardliner in the Israeli government as foreign minister. </seg>
<seg id=2> This appointment was made right before the Israeli and Palestinian leaders are going to hold a summit meeting on a provisional peace agreement in the United States. </seg>
<seg id=3> By the agreement, Israel shall return more land on the West Bank to Palestinians. </seg>
<seg id=4> Sharon firmly maintains that Jewish settlement be built up along the West Bank.  He also opposes making any compromise on withdrawing the troops. </seg>
</p>
